《'''反仿冒贸易协定'''》（{{lang-en|Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement}}，缩写{{lang|en|ACTA}}）是一个国际[[智慧財產權|智慧財產權]]协定<ref name="ec-fact-sheet-nov2008" />。自願加入的國家將建立一個國際法律框架，並建立一個國際機構以外的理事機構。該協定由[[日本|日本]]發起，並獲得各大行業巨頭的支持<ref name="mc" />。協定已於2011年底被多個[[已開發國家|已開發國家]]簽署。

ACTA在推出後被廣泛批評為限制人權、隱私權與言論自由的協議，並且在歐洲多處掀起了抗議。歐盟負責研究ACTA的專員也提出辭職並參與了抗議活動<ref name="NYT-20120205" /><ref name='Masnick 26 January 2011'>{{cite news | first = Mike | last = Masnick | title = European Parliament Official In Charge Of ACTA Quits, And Denounces The 'Masquerade' Behind ACTA | date = 26 January 2011 | url = http://www.techdirt.com/articles/20120126/11014317553/european-parliament-official-charge-acta-quits-denounces-masquerade-behind-acta.shtml | work = Techdirt | accessdate = 27 January 2012 | archive-date = 2012-01-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120129152229/http://www.techdirt.com/articles/20120126/11014317553/european-parliament-official-charge-acta-quits-denounces-masquerade-behind-acta.shtml | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name='Thomson 27 January 2012'>{{cite news | first = Iain | last = Thomson | title = Most EU states sign away internet rights, ratify ACTA treaty | date = 27 January 2012 | url = http://www.theregister.co.uk/2012/01/27/eu_signs_acta/ | work = The Register | accessdate = 27 January 2012 | archive-date = 2012-01-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120129230530/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2012/01/27/eu_signs_acta/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="IBTimes">{{cite news |title = Act against Acta: Demonstrators Protest against Poland Signing |url = http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/articles/287236/20120125/act-against-acta-demonstrators-protest-poland-signing.htm |newspaper = International Business Times |first = Gianluca |last = Mezzofiore |date = 25 January 2012 |accessdate = 25 January 2012 |archive-date = 2012-01-28 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120128091944/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/articles/287236/20120125/act-against-acta-demonstrators-protest-poland-signing.htm |dead-url = no }}</ref> 。反對者指出ACTA幕後的組織試圖以封鎖政治敏感的網站為誘餌換取簽署<ref name="mc" />。

== 背景 ==
ACTA是一個維護[[智慧財產權|智慧財產權]]的[[多邊協議|多邊協議]]，目的是为了全面加强[[国际贸易|国际贸易]]中[[智慧財產權|智慧財產權]]的保护<ref name="ec-fact-sheet-nov2008">{{cite web|title=Fact Sheet: Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement|publisher=European Commission|url=http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2008/october/tradoc_140836.11.08.pdf|date=23 October 2007 (Updated November 2008)|format=PDF|accessdate=27 November 2009|archive-date=2012-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120131151217/http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2008/october/tradoc_140836.11.08.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。自願加入的國家將建立一個國際法律框架<ref name="med.govt.nz" />，並建立一個類似於[[世界貿易組織|世界貿易組織]]和[[世界智慧財產權組織|世界智慧財產權組織]]國際機構以外的理事機構<ref name="ec-fact-sheet-nov2008"/><ref name=Pilieci>{{Cite news | last=Pilieci | first=Vito | title=Copyright deal could toughen rules governing info on iPods, computers | work=Vancouver Sun | location=Canada | date=26 May 2008 | accessdate=27 May 2008 | url=http://www.canada.com/vancouversun/story.html?id=ae997868-220b-4dae-bf4f-47f6fc96ce5e&p=1 | archive-date=2008-06-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080601022602/http://www.canada.com/vancouversun/story.html?id=ae997868-220b-4dae-bf4f-47f6fc96ce5e&p=1 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。談判的國家形容是對“全球貿易下的仿冒商品的增加和盜版的版權保護”的回應<ref name="med.govt.nz" />。ACTA的範圍包括[[仿冒|仿冒]]商品、[[仿製藥品|仿製藥品]]和網路上的[[侵權|侵權]]行為<ref name="ustr-acta-summary">{{cite web|author=USTR|authorlink=Office of the United States Trade Representative|title=The Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement – Summary of Key Elements Under Discussion|url=http://www.ustr.gov/sites/default/files/uploads/factsheets/2009/asset_upload_file917_15546.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=25 November 2009|postscript=|archive-date=2012-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201230245/http://www.ustr.gov/sites/default/files/uploads/factsheets/2009/asset_upload_file917_15546.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[電子前線基金會|電子前線基金會]]等團體反對ACTA<ref name="EFF ACTA">{{cite web |title=Sunlight for ACTA |publisher=EFF |url=http://www.eff.org/action/sunlight-acta |accessdate=5 July 2008 |archive-date=2012-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323012650/https://www.eff.org/action/sunlight-acta |dead-url=no }}</ref>，並指出[[非政府組織|非政府組織]]和[[開發中國家|開發中國家]]被排除在討論之外，ACTA的發展是一個[[政策洗钱|政策洗钱]]的例子<ref name="liftveil" />。
[[美國電影協會|美國電影協會]]是ACTA的重大幕後支持者，並且其在向[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]政府推銷ACTA時明確提出後者可以藉用ACTA封鎖令其難堪的網站，例如[[WikiLeaks|WikiLeaks]]<ref name="mc">{{cite news
