==評價==
===支持方===
支援ACTA的組織形容ACTA的目的是为了全面加强[[国际贸易|国际贸易]]中智慧財產權的保护<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2008/october/tradoc_140836.11.08.pdf|title="Fact Sheet: Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement"|publisher=European Commission|date=2007-10-23(更新2008年11月)|accessdate=2009年10月27日|archive-date=2010-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100331210353/http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2008/october/tradoc_140836.11.08.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>、以及對“全球貿易下的仿冒商品的增加和盜版的版權保護”的回應。ACTA的範圍包括仿冒商品、仿製藥品和網路上的侵權行為。G8峰會的發言中認為，盜版是一種「嚴重且有組織的犯罪」，<ref>{{cite web
|title=G8 Summit, Declaration on Growth and Economic Responsibility in the World Economy
|url=http://www.g-8.de/Content/EN/Artikel/__g8-summit/anlagen/2007-06-07-gipfeldokument-wirtschaft-eng,templateId=raw,property=publicationFile.pdf/2007-06-07-gipfeldokument-wirtschaft-eng.pdf
|accessdate=2012-06-19
|archive-date=2012-07-03
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120703100904/http://www.g-8.de/Content/EN/Artikel/__g8-summit/anlagen/2007-06-07-gipfeldokument-wirtschaft-eng,templateId=raw,property=publicationFile.pdf/2007-06-07-gipfeldokument-wirtschaft-eng.pdf
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>G8認為其反盜版的目的在於「保護消費者」，儘管有許多消費者在購買時已明知自己正在購買盜版商品。

===反對方===
====談判透明性====
[[電子前線基金會|電子前線基金會]]等團體反對ACTA，並指出[[非政府組織|非政府組織]]和開發中國家被排除在討論之外，ACTA的發展是一個[[政策洗钱|政策洗钱]]的例子<ref name='Geist 2008-06-09'>{{cite web | url = http://www.michaelgeist.ca/content/view/3013/135/ | title = Government Should Lift Veil on ACTA Secrecy | accessdate = 2012-01-29 | last = Geist | first = Michael | date = 2008-06-09 | archive-date = 2008-12-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081205070642/http://www.michaelgeist.ca/content/view/3013/135/ | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。
討論過程欠缺開發中國家的參與，主導的國家以[[美國|美國]]、[[日本|日本]]、[[歐盟|歐盟]]為首，三者都是大宗智慧財產權商品的出口國，如此的談判結果對於智慧財產權商品的進口國而言相當不利。

====人權憂慮====
反對者對這項協定可能對[[公民權利|公民權利]]、[[言論自由|言論自由]]、與[[隱私權|隱私權]]產生的影響表示擔憂<ref name="NYT-20120205">{{cite news |last=Jolly |first=David |title=A New Question of Internet Freedom |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/06/technology/06iht-acta06.html |date=5 February 2012 |publisher=NYTimes |accessdate=5 February 2012 |archive-date=2012-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208043251/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/06/technology/06iht-acta06.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name='FFII analysis'>{{cite news | title = The world faces major challenges | date = 18 December 2011 | url = http://action.ffii.org/acta/Analysis | publisher = Foundation for a Free Information Infrastructure | accessdate = 29 January 2012 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120129232412/http://action.ffii.org/acta/Analysis | archive-date = 2012-01-29 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref name="EDRi fundamental rights">{{cite web |url=http://www.edri.org/files/EDRI_acta_series_1_20120116.pdf |title=ACTA and its impact on fundamental rights |accessdate=5 February 2012 |date=16 January 2012 |format=PDF |publisher=European Digital Rights |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65DjZsK8f?url=http://www.edri.org/files/EDRI_acta_series_1_20120116.pdf |archivedate=2012-02-05 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name='Barengolts 2011-10-12'>{{cite news | first = Phillip | last = Barengolts | title = The Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement (ACTA) strives to strengthen protection for copyright and trademark owners throughout the world against counterfeiting and piracy of their products by attempting to harmonize the laws of member nations. But will it? | date = 2011-10-12 | publisher = [[Lexology|Lexology]] | url = http://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=83358d53-fbbb-47da-b936-a0271439a750 | work = Pattishall McAuliffe Newbury Hilliard & Geraldson LLP | accessdate = 2012-01-29 | archive-date = 2016-03-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305084517/http://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=83358d53-fbbb-47da-b936-a0271439a750 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="med.govt.nz">{{cite web|url=http://www.med.govt.nz/templates/ContentTopicSummary____34357.aspx|title=On Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement|author=Ministry of Economic Development of New Zealand|year=2008|accessdate=2012-01-30|archive-date=2011-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716072750/http://www.med.govt.nz/templates/ContentTopicSummary____34357.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="liftveil">{{cite web|first=Michael|last=Geist|title=Government Should Lift Veil on ACTA Secrecy|url=http://www.michaelgeist.ca/content/view/3013/135/|date=9 June 2008|accessdate=28 November 2008|archive-date=2008-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081205070642/http://www.michaelgeist.ca/content/view/3013/135/|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="freeo">{{cite web |url=http://freeknowledge.eu/acta-a-global-threat-to-freedoms-open-letter |title=ACTA: A Global Threat to Freedoms (Open Letter) | Free Knowledge Institute |publisher=Freeknowledge.eu |date= |accessdate=2012-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120130023554/http://freeknowledge.eu/acta-a-global-threat-to-freedoms-open-letter |archive-date=2012-01-30 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
反對者還批評ACTA移除了法律上對[[ISP|ISP]]進行保護，免於用戶行為上的法律責任，實際上使ISP業者無從選擇，只能遵守並且侵犯個人隱私<ref name="problem">{{Cite journal|first=Aaron|last=Shaw|title=The Problem with the Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement (and what to do about it)|url=http://kestudies.org/node/20/|journal=KEStudies|volume=2|date=April 2009|author=|access-date=2012-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215065354/http://www.kestudies.org/node/20|archive-date=2012-02-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。
根據由[[自由軟體基金會|自由軟體基金會]]分析表示，ACTA會要求現有ISP業者不再提供可以訪問受版权或[[數位內容權利管理|數位內容權利管理]]保护媒体的免費軟體，免費軟體和[[開源軟體|開源軟體]]將被禁止使用<ref name="fsf-speak-out">{{cite web|url=http://www.fsf.org/campaigns/acta/|title=Speak out against ACTA|publisher=Free Software Foundation|accessdate=2012-02-02|archive-date=2012-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120202044422/http://www.fsf.org/campaigns/acta/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

====自由貿易====
153位[[世界貿易組織|世界貿易組織]]成員大部分都對该条约可能扭曲贸易，并超越[[與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定|與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定]]方面上的现有协定表示關注<ref name="lynn">{{cite web| last = Lynn| first = Jonathan| title = States clash over anti-counterfeiting enforcement| publisher = Reuters| date = 9 June 2010| url = http://in.reuters.com/article/idINIndia-49179920100609| accessdate = 12 June 2010| archive-date = 2010-09-06| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100906155952/http://in.reuters.com/article/idINIndia-49179920100609| dead-url = no}}</ref>。超越[[與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定|與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定]]的規範稱為"TRIPS-Plus"，ACTA的疑慮在於越過[[與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定|與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定]]大會討論，而由智慧財產權商品的出口國所主導，片面協商訂立有利於[[與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定|與貿易有關的智慧財產權協定]]權利擁有者方之條文。

